        <skos:altLabel>&lt;111&gt; || ND</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">γ-fibre grain orientation is a type of grain orientation which is quality of polycrystal, i.e., several grains, oriented in the following way: &lt;111&gt; family of crystallographic directions are oriented parallel to the normal direction (ND) of a sheet material, i.e., normal to the rolling plane.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


